  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">The absorption cross section of natural Gd and isotopic enriched 157 Gd for ultra-cold neutrons (UCN) as a function of the velocity has been measured within a time-of-flight-experiment. Particular attention is paid to small velocities in the region of a few m/s. This is intended to determine the validity of the <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mn>1</mn><mo stretchy="false">/</mo><mi>v</mi></math> -law governing absorption cross sections in this region and the resulting divergence at <math altimg="si2.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math> . The experiment does not show any significant violation of <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mn>1</mn><mo stretchy="false">/</mo><mi>v</mi></math> for <math altimg="si3.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi>v</mi><mo>></mo><mn>3</mn><mtext> </mtext><mtext>m</mtext><mo stretchy="false">/</mo><mtext>s</mtext></math> .</subfield>
